==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Patera
<hw>Pat"e*ra</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Pater⟦ae⟧</plw>(<?/).</plu> <ety>[L., fr. <ets>patere</ets> to lie
open.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A saucerlike vessel of earthenware or
metal, used by the Greeks and Romans in libations and
sacrifices.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Arch.)</fld> <def>A circular ornament, resembling a
dish, often worked in relief on friezes, and the like.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Paterero</ent>⟦br⟧
